               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Libānos “Vita of Libānos” (fols. 3ra–47va)&#xD;
II) Taʾāmra Libānos “Miracles of Libānos”: 11 miracles, preceded by a short praise to Libānos (fols. 47vb–62vb[l.4])&#xD;
III) Mälkәʾa Libānos “Image of Libānos”: 29 strophes (fols. 62vb[l.10]–65rb).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For the Texts of Gadla Libānos, Taʾāmra Libānos and Malkǝʾa Libānos compare them to the edited version: A. BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003 (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]).</note>
                     <note>- Text II is preceded by a short praise (on <locus target="47va">47va</locus>, ls. 3-19) in honour of the Saint. It is written in a smaller script but most probably by the same hand.</note>
                     <note>- In the incipits of the Miracles (Text II), both names of the protagonist (Libānos and Mäṭaʿ) are alternatively used.</note>
                     <note>Lacuna between Text II and Text III (<locus target="62vb">62vb</locus>, ls. 4-9).</note>
                     <note>- In Text III, as compared to the edited version (cp. A. BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003a (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]),<ref type="mss" corresp="ES206212">206-212</ref>[text] and<ref type="mss" corresp="ES119122">119-122</ref>[tr.]), one strophe at the end is missing.</note>
                     <note>- The ultimate portion of Text III is written on the first (unruled) leaf of quire B, probably by the hand different from that of the main text (hand a).</note>
                     <note>- A ruled line at the bottom was not used by the scribe, on <locus from="3r" to="10v">3r-10v</locus>, 35r-36v.</note>
                     <note>- The rubrication is mostly carried out in reddish-brown; the ink used for the names of the donors is of somewhat different tones (e.g., cp. Walda Mikāʾel, <locus target="36ra">36ra</locus>, l.17, and Za-Walda Māryām, <locus target="55vb">55vb</locus>, l.3).</note>
                  </msItem>
